We further set out to investigate the structural features of HKU23-NTD via crystallography. The protein was successfully crystallized in space group C2, and the structure was eventually determined at the resolution of 2.5 angstrom (Å) (Table 1
) by molecular replacement using the structure of the NTD protein from BCoV (BCoV-NTD) (PDB code: 4H14) as the search model. High-quality electron density map enables us to unambiguously model the whole polypeptide chain of HKU23-NTD extending from V15 to K298. These amino acids fold into a compact structure, which can be further divided into a large β-sandwich core and several peripheral structural elements (Fig. 2
).
